  "text": "We had shown previously that a similar alteration in fibronectin retention and organization occurred in the parental cells upon exposure to exogenous gangliosides, particularly GM~, Gr,~, and GT~b (36, [CITATION_1] . We therefore examined the different sublines for endogenous cell surface gangliosides. The cells were exposed in situ to mild periodate oxidation and then reduction with KB3I-I4 of very high specific radioactivity in order to label surface sialic acid residues (9, 26, 29) 1. The gangliosides then were isolated, separated by thin-1. Previous attempts to label cell surface gangliosides of NCTC 2071A cells were unsuccessful due to the use of NaB3I-h of much lower specific radioactivity (29). Consistent with our present results, small amounts of Gu2 were detected in these cells [CITATION_2] 21, 28) , layer chromatography, and detected by fluorography. Substantial amounts of 3H w e r e incorporated into the ganglioside fractions isolated from the oxidized cells; in the absence of periodate, there was very little incorporation (Fig. 3) . The gangliosides were tentatively identified by their migration on the chromatogram relative to reference gangliosides. [CITATION_3] In the parental cells (Fig. 3, lane 6 ), the majority of the radioactivity was located in the GM2 zone I but radioactivity also was detected in the GM3 zone. After a longer exposure, there was a trace of JH in the GM, zone but none was detectable in the more complex gangliosides such as Gr,,a and GT~b (data not shown). In the case of the variant cells (Fig. 3, lane 4) , GM~ was the predominate radioactive zone but it was much more extensively labeled than the corresponding zone from the parental cells. Incorporation of 3H into Gra3 and GMt also was increased compared to the parental gangliosides. The most striking differences were the appearance of labeled gangliosides corresponding to Gol~ and Gx~b. The ganglioside fraction from the revertant ceils also exhibited increased labeling of the GM3, GM2, GMI, and GD~a zones compared to the parental gangliosides but the incorporation of 3H was less prominant than that observed with the variant cells and there was very little labeling of the GT,b zone (Fig. 3, lane 5) .",
